 	\lim_{x \to -2} \frac{x^2-4}{x^2+3x+2} = \lim_{x \to -2} f(x) \\ 	f(x) = \frac{(x-2)(x+2)}{(x+2)(x+1)} = 		\begin{cases} 			\frac{x-2}{x+1},& x \neq -2 \\ 			\varnothing,& x = -2 		\end{cases} \\ 	\lim_{x \to -2} f(x) = \frac{-2-2}{-2+1}=\frac{-4}{-1}=4 
\varnothing
