\lim_{x \to -2} \frac{x^2 - 4}{x^2 + 3x + 2} = \lim_{x \to -2} \frac{(x-2)(x+2)}{(x+1)(x+2)} = \lim_{x \to -2} \frac{x-2}{x+1} = \frac{-4}{-1}=4.
